,Recommended,285310,19350857,"Posted: 28 November, 2015",all,Prizm,"As a kid I would always start off every park I made by hiring 5 or so handymen, in preparation for the onslaught of puke and overfilled garbage bins the park would soon be plagued with. And yet, I always made sure to remove the ""mow grass"" from their job descriptions; keeping it meant your handymen would be off mowing instead of doing everything else. And yet, I always felt bad for the grass; was it really right to neglect it, simply because of a minor inconveniance to my park? So I always hired one more than I needed, and made his only job being to mow grass. 35$ monthly, earned solely through his sweat and his lawnmower. Off in the unexplored regions of the park, where nobody can even see the grass he's mowing. I always made sure to give him a absurd name.Around 10 years later, I find myself tracking Dorkle's adventure through the wilderness, chronicling his neverending battle against the grass, as I try to find a good spot for the next ferris wheel.10/10 would relive cherised childhood memories again."
