,Recommended,285310,17344182,"Posted: 1 August, 2015",all,NoahTheGuy,"A charming and timeless game, Rollercoaster Tycoon will continue to please the young at heart and theme park fans today. The Pre-Rendered graphics still hold up to this day better than most games of it's time. The most impressive thing about this game is the development of it. It was programmed by one man; Chris Sawyer. The highlight of this game is seeing your guests come off your ride enjoying themselves. It is a very rewarding experience. That's not to say this game is without faults. One of the bigger problems is the limitation of scenery. This was however fixed in the game's sequels, and if we go into nitpicking, there are problems with the janitors only mowing grass (which can be easily fixed by checking a box). These things can be overlooked however and I believe that this entry in the series is by far the most rewarding. I haven't sunk as many hours into this game as the other entries but that doesn't mean I haven't had fun the entire time, grinning like an idiot ear to ear8/10"
