76561198073720466,Recommended,285310,35159086,Posted: 23 September,all,higgsbosonman,"So to everybody having issues getting this to run on windows 10, there is an easy solution.go to control panel > programs and featureson the left side of the screen, you'll see ""Turn Windows Features On or Off"". click it.You'll get a menu with a bunch of check boxes. go to ""Legacy Components"" and expand the folder, and make sure DirectPlay is enabled. then enable the ""Legacy Components"" folder as well if it isnt (it should have a check mark, not a black box).once DirectPlay and Legacy Components have been enabled, the game should play.As for the review itself, this game is exactly like I remember it, and its super fun and nostalgic for me. I'm super happy with it and oddly enough, it runs really smooth on a computer thats 15 years newer than the game :D"
