76561198005642884,Recommended,285310,28199342,"Posted: 4 December, 2016",all,kitty0ncrack,"This game is a whole lot of wonderful nostolgia.  I would sink endless hours into this game as a kid, and as computers got newer getting the thing to work was harder and harder. Then steam came out with this! Completely worth the 6 bucks! And it even has the 2 expansion packs to boot!This game is old, so bear in mind it's isometic rather than 3D so if you are used to a free-form camera you may need a moment to adjust to having it locked at 90 degree angles. However, I never found myself struggling to place objects because of the camera.The AI is.... not the best.  Your park layout has to be, for the most part, a strait line or a large circle.  Otherwise your park guests get lost. However, I don't find this takes away from the game. Placing information kiosks and using monorails or chairlifts help with this ""guest 102 is lost and can't find the park exit"" nonsense.A great feature is any alert it gives you, good or bad, you can bring the camera to that spot. Lost guest? pick him up and show him the park exit.Despite it's age the coaster design part of the game is still my favorite.  A good variety of coasters, options, designs, I can truly build the monster coasts of my dreams. And make incomplete ones that rocket guests to their dooms like a total sadist.If you were a fan of the game a a kid, totally dive back in it's a wonderful game.  And to anyone curious about trying it for the first time, it's an excellent simulation game and you really can let your creativity shine.ONLY issue I ever encountered: The game will strobe if you have the program F.lux running. This is a program to dim your monitor to yellow-toned colors at night to reduce eye strain.  But it's incompatible with this game. All you need to do is disable F.lux before firing up the game and you will have zero issues."
