,Recommended,285310,14131540,"Posted: 23 January, 2015",all,EnnuiBo,"I am one of the few players to have owned Roller Coaster Tycoon since March 31st, 1999. This game IS my childhood, it wasnt a part of it, but it was my life as a child.RCT has taken a huge chunk of my life away, as I have spent thousands of hours creating parks, creating scenarios and editing custom content. And im here to tell you after nearly 16 years of gameplay, why you should buy and cherish this relic.The objective is simple. Build the theme park of your dreams. But it goes much deeper then it seems. There's staff to manage, bills to pay, capital to gain, advertisements to be used, and new rides to be build. RCT is simply not a reskin of Theme Park, it's a buisness simulator underneath a Theme Park simulator. It's extremely open ended and there is no TRUE endgame, other then beating all the parks. It is litterally endless thanks to the support of custom content and scenarios that are always popping up through the internet.Many people have complained about the steam port lacking compatibility with Windows 7/8. I have yet to run into any serious issues with the port. The only thing that HAS YET to work is the Steam Overlay, but it's to be expected.In all, Buy the game. Play it, introduce your children to it. Enjoy it."
