,Recommended,285310,25538298,"Posted: 16 September, 2016",all,Dr. Lazarus,"Important note: If you have problems loading this game, consider installing OpenRCT2.  Not only can it help you run this game (and Rollercoaster Tycoon 2), it adds many features that did not exist in the original.This game was very fun when it first came out, and it is still fun now.  Before Rollercoaster Tycoon, the best (only?) theme park sim was Theme Park.  That game was decent, but Rollercoaster Tycoon was a huge step forward in the genre.  The game has aged very well, and still holds up today.  Whether you want to build the most elaborate coasters, build the biggest parks, or just want to drown your customers or immolate them with a coaster destined to crash in a fiery explosing, grab this game if you do not already own it."
