76561198006568104,Recommended,285310,19116864,"Posted: 16 November, 2015",all,Morgoth,"For more reviews and gameplay videos by Morgoth, check out mySteam profile, theYoutube channel, and theTwitch channel!!What more can be said about this game, that hasn't been said a thousand times before?  This is an incredible game that is easily worth the six dollars that it currently cost.  Even if you are not big into simulation games (like myself), this game will quickly catch your attention and it will not surrender it for quite some time.  Before you realize it, 4 hours have passed.  If anything this game is dangerous for how easily it erases massive amounts of time.I was going to write up another big, long review for this game but as I stated before, everything that could be said about how incredible this game is, has been said.  So I'll keep it short and sweet.Gameplay:Very seemingly simplistic gameplay, but with oh so much depth.  Enough to keep coming back to for days, weeks, months, years....  you get the idea.  Build a park.  Aim for the objective (# of customers, customer approval rating, etc.).  Win the game.  Play forever if you wish.  The UI that is implemented here is very user-friendly and makes building even the most ridiculous elaborate parks very simplistic.Graphics:Great graphics for the time when it was released (1999).  Runs perfectly on even the oldest of machines with no fps drops.  This game was made so incredibly stable because Chris Sawyer sat it fit to program the entire game in Assembly language.  Which is ridiculously awesome and very, VERY difficult to do, but in doing so, made the game incredibly efficient and available to a massive audience.  The game does run on every Windows OS up to Windows 10 x64 (because that's what I played it on).  Might have to mess with the resolution though.Sound:The park guests' sounds of approval, or of wretching on the sidewalk, does fit perfectly into the game, and it does give off the theme park vibe very adequately.  However, the music that can be played from the rides gets repetitive very quickly.Lasting Appeal:Holy lord don't even get me started on the lasting appeal of this game.  Not only is there the ability to play the parks forever, but in this deluxe package with the two expansions, there are over 70 FREAKING PARKS.  THAT'S value.  To give an example of how much time would be sunk into the game in that time, it would be close to 250 hours.  And that's only if you somehow manage to beat every scenario first try.  So yeah, it's got some lasting appeal.Final Verdict:This game is incredible.  It was amazing in 1999, and it's amazing in 2015.  And it will be amazing in 2025.9.5/10"
