76561198102352454,Recommended,285310,31663719,Posted: 10 May,all,Countersnipe,"One of the best games that you should never buy.The only issue with this game - and by issue I mean MASSIVE ISSUE - is that you cannot speed up time. The game gives you objectives to reach on each map, and in order to unlock the new maps to play you must reach the objectives of the previous maps. However, you will often find that you reach the objectives well before the deadline, but because you cannot speed up time you cannot move forward and hand in your objective to complete the map.This is kind of a really big deal because you will often find that your objective has been met, but it will be anywhere from 1-2 hours of real time before your objetive is due... I have 22 hours worth of playtime, but I think I've only spend 4 hours of time actually playing the game - I ususally just minimize the game and have it run in the background until the objective date is met.With this said - this is a fantastic game with one major major flaw. To some people, this isn't a big deal as they just play the scenario and keep building the park. but for me, I'm super objective oriented and I want to progress once I have achieved a goal... To be stuck in the map knowing I've already beaten it is super annoying."
