76561198186646265,Recommended,285310,18571610,"Posted: 19 October, 2015",all,Justin Hineman,"Let me begin by saying that I have been an avid Payday fan since the first installment starting around early 2013. I played the hell out of the first game and when I heard the second was on the way around April of 2013, I couldn't have been more excited. I put in a pre-order for the Career Criminal Edition and played the beta prior to release. Once the game came out, I dumped lots of time into it. Although I'd get burnt out on it and have to take breaks for about a week or two at a time, I kept coming back to it. I was always so inspired by the devs at Overkill to do like they had, and for the past few months my friend and I have been making our own game. It's not anything much at this point but people like Simon and Almir made me passionate about games and I chose to persue that path for myself. Watching this game evolve from the beginning has been incredible, and although it's had some bad moments, we can't deny that it has had some kickass moments as well. But not anymore. Now that Overkill has made the bright decision to put microtransactions into the game, I've never been more disappointed in them. The least they could've done is ignored the questions about microtransactions, but even so, going against their word is sickening. I can no longer recommend this masterpiece product to others because they turned it into♥♥♥♥♥♥with the addition of paying more money. I mean seriously, there's already enough DLC for this game to starve your bank account, and then they decide to pull this? I don't think so. Sorry Overkill, you guys really ♥♥♥♥ing blew it this time."
