,Recommended,285310,11289088,"Posted: 17 July, 2014",all,Neslope♀,"Before I get more in-depth, I'll explain my opinions on the RCT games for anyone unsure on what to get. If you're looking for a fun and challenging campaign-based RCT, buy this one. If you want lots of mods and custom scenarios to toy with, buy 2. And last, if you want MORE mods, more realistic theme park recreations, water parks, zoo parks, and lots of sandbox coaster building, buy 3. I think all are good, but each has its strong points.But anyways, this is the original RCT, with all the expansions and a bunch of fan-made tracks added on. To put it short, it's a good game. The only major problems with this version are its quirks when used with Windows 7 and 8. The game, from what I know, will only run in a square resolution unless you change the inner workings of the EXE. It can crash fairly often, for semi-random reasons. And my install sometimes glitches my desktop when I quit, forcing me to reboot.However, if you can look past some irritating glitches on newer OSes, then this is a must-have. For about the same price as a CD of the game, you get everything on it already on your hard drive, no CD insertion required. If you're a big RCT fan, then I'd say buy it."
