,Recommended,285310,15303400,"Posted: 11 April, 2015",all,SpazmanianDevil,"My room mate recently started replaying this game and seeing as Steam had it I bought it and started playing it again as well.Ahhh~ The nolstagia is strong with this game.Your main goal with this game is to build up and maintain a them park while following the guidelines of each level. Some start you from scratch, others don't. Anyway, it's a simple but complicated game as most Management type games go. For instance, can't make a roller coaster too scary or hardly anyone will ride it but if it's too weak, no one will want to ride it because it's not intense enough. Just be sure to Test Run your ride first to make sure it isn't a death trap. I've accidentally killed some people because I forgot to do that first. >_> Sometimes it's really hard to know if what you're building will appeal to your guests, but once you've got it right, advertise the crap out of your new ride, and watch the dollars signs fly up.Anyway, this game is enjoyable and relaxing. If you likebuilding and maintaining and feeling powerful because you know how to maintain a park and make big bucks doing it, then this game is for you.P.S. If you click on a stray balloon it will pop and if you click on a duck, it will quack. I didn't know about these fun little Easter Eggs until I bought it on Steam so I thought I would share that with you. :) Have fun!"
