76561198168918255,Recommended,285310,23460877,"Posted: 8 June, 2016",all,A Mug,"RollerCoaster Tycoon: Deluxe is the First installment of the RollerCoaster Tycoon Franchise. This game was made I believe late 1990's or early 2000's, with pretty good graphics and programming, made by one guy (Chris Sawyer).I remember when I first started playing this game when I was 7 years old, I had no idea what I was doing, but I had fun messing around until I went bankrupt or something. Now I know how to properly manage a park, and respond to the guests' demands, as well as making sure I make a nice and steady profit.This game still holds up really well IMO, and is nice to kill some time when you got nothing to do or anything like that. The game is also very realistic, people react to what happens in the park, not entirely, but functionally. Here's to name a few things:1. If a RollerCoaster crashes (Accidentally), some people will leave the park and the ride's popularity will plumet to 0%2. A ride's intensity and price will affect whether a guest will ride it or not (Some guests like intense rides, some don't)3. When you begin building more than 3 (Good) RollerCoasters, guests will start to no longer want to pay more than $1.00 for less thrilling rides.Just to name some things---(Also, Employees get paid less than minumum wage on this game, so be glad you don't live in a RollerCoaster Tycoon world, or you'll be living with $35-$50 a month)Overall, it's a good gameIf you like RollerCoasters, Tycoons, and CHEAP games, then give this one a try."
