76561198080726571,Recommended,285310,21223743,"Posted: 14 February, 2016",all,Jek the Snek,"Pros:. Addicting. Very nice graphics/sound aesthetic. Hundreds of hours of gameplay, not including replay value. Feeling of progression through scenarios that the sequel does not have. The satisfying feeling of seeing people enter and interact with an amusement park that you built. You can create your own theme park!Cons:. Selections of attractions to build feel a bit limited at times. Isometric view with no shadows makes building/landscaping a bit tedious at times. Scenario objectives mostly constrained to achieving a certain number of guests/park value. Most of the scenarios are very easy (however this doesn't take away from the fun at all) while the others are extremely difficult. Essentially, not a great difficulty curve.The pros overshadow the cons. In other words, the pros enhance the experience more than the cons take away from it.Extra note: If you've never played before, make sure you look up some strategies or gameplay footage (Zisteau being the best to watch in my opinion) before you do. Trust me."
