,Recommended,285310,20428073,"Posted: 9 January, 2016",all,Neutron,"I already own the original game but I decided to buy it on here for the convenience of having it on steamBefore I bought it, I had hoped that Atari would have done some light overhauling of the game to make it more fit for modern computers by enabing higher resolutions, adding the ability to save unlocked parks to steam, steam overlay support and just general compatibility improvements. But they've not done any of that, it's just the same as the original, so any technical issues you have with the original, you're going to have with this version too. Most of the time it runs without any issues, but remember that this game was originally written for Windows 95.If you already own the original game, this is not really worth it as you're not paying for an overhauled version like you may be hoping. You're literally just getting ripped off by paying up for the exact same thing again. It feels a bit like they've just gotten a cracked version of the game and stuck it up on here for sale.Also, this is the US version of the game, so it uses the US park and ride names. It doesn't support all the same languages that the UK/EU version did. Swedish is missing, for example.With that said, this is one of my favourite childhood games and is still an excellent games that will serve you with countless hours of enjoyment. If you don't have the original discs, go ahead and buy it!"
