,Recommended,285310,28886104,"Posted: 31 December, 2016",all,FlowingMindspin,"Man, what a deal this is -- I paid $50 or so for this when it was new over a decade ago, and then bought the expansions separately after that. Fast forward to now and while I can find the discs, they're scratched up and my computer won't read them properly half the time. I got this for $2.49 on sale and it is very much worth that price. Hell, I'd say it's worth ten times that when you look at the amount of scenarios and content this game has.For the uninitiated, you build a theme park... sometimes from scratch, sometimes adding on to an existing park. Some scenarios require you to have a certain amount of guests, a certain park rating, or increase the value of the park by a certain amount before a year or more has passed in the game. There are dozens of attractions, coasters, rides, and shops to place into your park and quite a few besides just the roller coasters allow you to construct a ride of your own design (other ""build your own"" rides include a boat hire, train, monorail, car ride, log flume, and water slides), and there are a dozen or so types of coasters on top of that.Building and running a successful park is a balancing act of proper pricing, layout, marketing, and well-designed custom rides. You can't just make a coaster with a 90 foot drop that sends your patrons through all kinds of madness at 80 mph -- they won't get on it because it's too scary. A successful coaster has lots of different elements (hills, banked turns, helixes, tunnels, loops, and what have you), goes through those elements at the proper speed, and has scenery and theming that add to the ride's excitement (like rushing through a row of trees after a big drop, or a loop that has a track going through it).I feel like I could talk about this game forever... in short, if you like building things, buy this game. If you like theme park sims, buy this game. If you are put off by the dated graphics (which still look pretty darn good to me), buy this game anyway and be surprised at the depth and amount of content there is.I can't recommend this game enough."
