,Recommended,285310,34248391,Posted: 14 August,all,HolyJunkie,"Dear Diary:Day 1: Today is the first day of my new job: An animal mascot in this brand-new park, called ""EMPTY YOUR POCKETS, KIDS!"" Hey, it must be an effective name because it certainly got this guy a better job than doing tricks off the curb for fifty cents a blow. This day was mainly dedicated to orientation, some quick training on how to handle kids with problems, and also refreshing my skills in CPR. Here I come, world!Day 2: When I first saw the manager, I was expecting a fat slob with cheeto dust cascading down his chin like an avalanche. Instead, it was a skinny guy who looked weirdly like Mr. Burns. He didn't literally look like him, of course, but there was this aura to him. His eyes met mine and I suddenly had a feeling of pure dread. I'm sure it must've been remembering this one guy who grabbed the back of my head and... well... I'm certainly glad that last job is behind me.The manager walked up to me and pointed to an elevated scaffolding sitting in the middle of the lake. ""You're assigned there,"" he spoke with a silky, caramel-like voice.""But how will I reach the kids?"" I asked. I suddenly felt myself being lifted by the neck of my mascot costume! I managed to twist the head around to get a look, and it was THIS DISEMBODIED FLOATING CLAW RIGHT OUT FROM AN ARCADE MACHINE! It took me higher and higher, farther and farther away, until it finally dropped me directly onto this tiny platform sitting in the middle of a huge lake.At least it wasn't tuggies and blowies, I said to myself.Day 21: I'm still up here. I wake up, and I see strange things happening throughout the park. An entire corner is nothing but Go-kart tracks. All of them named ""MONEY SINK"". Children flock to the short lines, over and over and over again. The children spend hours and hundreds of dollars, at any of the Money Sinks. What the hell is happening with this park? There's not even a roller coaster yet! The only other rides I can see from up here are a merry-go-round, a ferris wheel, and countless concession stands!One of the twenty handimen are lifted here daily by that disembodied crane, and he brings me food and water. I ask him when I can go down and see the kids. However, every day it is a different handiman, and I could've sworn the latest one was wearing a plastic mask.At least it isn't tuggies and blowies...Day 59: the Money Sinks have multiplied, as have the crowds. Countless children from all around the country are getting ripped off from these rip-off go-kart rides. They don't even last a second! They make one loop and screech to a halt! Why is that manager building these things?At least it isn't tuggies and blowies... at least it isn't tuggies and blowies.Day 123: I know why the manager built the money sinks. I wake up today, and I see three enormous go-kart tracks. Each of them unique in design, twisting and turning, with tunnels through the earth, and bridges over the waters. From this platform, I can see the splendour in the craftsmanship. I can see that the tracks are simply experiences no human should life without.I look at the line-ups, and they're entirely empty. I am puzzled as to why. They are magnificent! They are far superior to tuggies and blowies!Day 124: The manager flies up to the platform via the disembodied claw. He tells me I'm fired, because I haven't been entertaining the children..........""Can I ride on one of those go-kart tracks?"" I ask.""No,"" he replied, ""This isn't Roller Coaster Tycoon 3."""
